{"questionId":"1251310","questionHtml":"<p>A glass block has a refractive index in air of <em>n</em><sub>g</sub>. The glass block is placed in two different liquids:&nbsp;liquid X with a refractive index of <em>n</em><sub>X</sub> and liquid Y with a refractive index of <em>n</em><sub>Y</sub>.</p>\n<p>In liquid X&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>g</mtext></msub><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;and in liquid Y&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>g</mtext></msub><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo></math>&nbsp;What is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mtext>speed&nbsp;of&nbsp;light&nbsp;in&nbsp;liquid&nbsp;X</mtext><mtext>speed&nbsp;of&nbsp;light&nbsp;in&nbsp;liquid&nbsp;Y</mtext></mfrac></math>?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"1251310","referenceCode":"21M.1A.SL.TZ2.16","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A glass block has a refractive index in air of ng. The glass block is placed in two different liquids: liquid X with a refractive index of nX and liquid Y with a refractive index o","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"16","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["C. Wave behaviour","C.3 Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}